{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, blockchain technology is still in its early stages, and significant organizational, legal, and technological constraints impede its full potential in healthcare 4.",
    "Although the 5G networking system and the Blockchain are two unique technical approaches, there are use scenarios and possible affinities where adding the Blockchain to the 5G networking system might improve networking mechanism.",
    "Blockchain authentication provides an immutable record of device authentication, making it difficult for hackers to breach; the key benefit of this integration is offering security and authentication processes within the 5G network system.",
    "Again, network segmentation is possible in 5G networks, and in these virtual network slices, the Blockchain may be utilized to govern service-level agreements and guarantee fair compensation for the networking system.",
    "Additionally, the Blockchain technique guarantees the decentralized 5G network, where the 5G may run without human involvement to assure network connectivity in the locations where human entry is challenging."
  ]
}